AI Linux - README

About the Project

AI Linux is a powerful tool for log analysis and error diagnostics with support for modern AI models. It combines Electron for the frontend, Flask for the backend, and various AI models for log file processing.

Installation

1. Install Prerequisites

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip git nodejs npm

2. Clone Project and Install Dependencies

git clone https://github.com/derleiti/ailinux.git
cd ailinux
pip install -r requirements.txt
npm install

3. Start Backend

cd backend
python app.py

4. Start Frontend

cd ../frontend
npm start

Usage

Start Log Analysis: Enter logs via the Electron interface and analyze them with AI models.

Manage Settings: Configure API keys and mode (CPU/GPU) in the settings.

Use Twitch Integration: The Twitch bot can automatically respond to chat messages.

Retrieve Logs:

curl http://localhost:8081/logs

Technology Stack

Backend: Python, Flask

Frontend: Electron, HTML, CSS, JavaScript

AI Models: OpenAI GPT-4, LLaMA, Google Gemini

Communication: WebSockets, REST API

